Labels.Label: zChoosesCPUCarFromFrameCounter
Labels.Comment:
This routine makes the probability skewed
because it has 1/4 of chance for each car
but, if the 1/4 chance chooses P1 car,
then it will wait one NMI cycle and 
always choose the next car. So, the chances are:

1/2: Next car
1/4: Other car 1
1/4: Other car 2

For instance, if P1 is red, then:
1/2: White
1/4: Purple
1/4: Blue

Also, this is VERY inefficient, as it waits
a whole frame 1/4 of the time. Changing
   BEQ $9281
for
   INC
   NOP
would have the same effect but not wait the frame.

The only possible reasoning for that
is that the frame counter cannot be on that mod 4 value
or else things would break.
Is it equal to P1 car?

If yes, loop, else:
If the code enter this loop, it will wait
all the way to the NMI to increase this
frame counter and exit the loop

The first element is the car that is

Labels.Label: zWhatIs1EEC_3
Labels.Comment:
Gets here sometimes some frames
after hitting road obstacles

It kinds of counter-steer what happens
at $F70B

Will store
#$B000 if the car is on the right side
or #$5000 if the car is on the left side

This probably turns the car inwards when
it hits the obstacles on the side of
the road, helping the player to get back
on track

In the game, we see that the car is pushed
inwards, but points outwards.

Also, cacti does not bring the code
here, while small bushes, signs
and small yellow balls do.

Enter here when some obstacle crashes
happens before in the frame

Changing this to NOP
makes some of the collisions with
another cars do not happen.

If $E4B6 is changed to NOP too, then
all collision with cars cease.

Got this info from
"Don't slow down against cars"
cheat

Changing this to NOP
makes some of the collisions with
another cars do not happen.

If $E4BB is changed to NOP too, then
all collision with cars cease.
